main event: A round white object the size of a nickel was seen on a downward course moving rapidly to the west.
interesting points: The object was still in sight at the time of the report.
The description, duration, and flight path indicate the object was probably a balloon or a 'nickel star'.
The observer was an Alpine Ranger Station house view.
The weather conditions were clear with a wind speed of 32 knots.
No photographs were taken of the object.
sighted object: round white object the size of a nickel
